    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Chinese script that evolved from the draft cursive script, and began to appear during the final years of the Han dynasty in the 2nd century CE. Its creation was accredited to Zhang Zhi and was later perfected by Wang Xizhi and his son Xianzhi in the 4th century CE. It is characterized by accelerated writing, continuous strokes, fluid movements, and expressiveness.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
